\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces State-space timeline of the tool magazine. Here, tool $t_1$ is safely retained across its 0-block (strictly during jobs $j_2$ and $j_3$) because the magazine capacity is large enough to accommodate the transition tools. This flips the 0-block to 1s in the state space, avoiding redundant unloading and reloading operations.}}{4}{figure.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:state_space_timeline}{{2}{4}{State-space timeline of the tool magazine. Here, tool $t_1$ is safely retained across its 0-block (strictly during jobs $j_2$ and $j_3$) because the magazine capacity is large enough to accommodate the transition tools. This flips the 0-block to 1s in the state space, avoiding redundant unloading and reloading operations}{figure.caption.2}{}}
